es. | MUST | T1 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\\\\\\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:112:| CCH-032 | Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. | SHOULD | T2 | - narrative beat → SectionEnvelope mapping exposed via existing narrative engine interface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\\\\\\\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:119:| CCH-039 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | MUST | T1 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\\\\\\\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-018_20260416T054258Zb_1776371017.log:48:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-16T20:24:39.142Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"tool_id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command_1776371042532_0\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"success\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.11/site-packages/pytest_asyncio/plugin.py:252: PytestDeprecationWarning: The configuration option \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"asyncio_default_fixture_loop_scope\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" is unset.\\\\\\\\\